                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.77/3669: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bell</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1924-10-13T15:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 13, 1924—3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>237. Your 382, October 10, 4 p.m. The Department does not perceive that any
                    further action in this matter would be warranted, and considers it unlikely that
                    such action would produce any good result. Advise Consuls at Mukden and
                    Harbin.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
